<subSubSection id="C34925AFFFFB066D0D9715EA3773D0AB" box="[199,1041,1413,1439]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BEC7624FFFB066D0D9715EA3773D0AB" blockId="13.[151,1437,908,1583]" box="[199,1041,1413,1439]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
<emphasis id="B927AA36FFFB066D0D9715EA322AD0AB" bold="true" box="[199,328,1413,1439]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Etymology</emphasis>
: In reference to the distinctive, laterally expanded hypandrium.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C34925AFFFFB066D0D9715C733A8D31B" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BEC7624FFFB066D0D9715C733A8D31B" blockId="13.[151,1437,908,1583]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
<emphasis id="B927AA36FFFB066D0D9715C7322AD0F7" bold="true" box="[199,328,1448,1475]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Comments</emphasis>
: “P.N.G.” on the label appears to refer to Garamba National park, which borders 
<collectingCountry id="F34436B4FFFB066D09B315C63614D0F7" box="[1251,1398,1449,1475]" name="South Sudan" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">South Sudan</collectingCountry>
. H. De Saeger was an entomologist and secretary of national parks in the 
<collectingCountry id="F34436B4FFFB066D0EEB15A2376AD0D3" box="[955,1032,1485,1511]" name="Democratic Republic of the Congo" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Congo</collectingCountry>
, who led many collecting trips and long-term ecological studies in that park. The “II/fd/17” on the label apparently is a code referring to a park location.
</paragraph>
